## üß™ How to Test

```bash
# 1. Start the development server
npm run dev

# 2. Open browser DevTools (F12)
# - Check Console tab - should see NO debug logs

# 3. Test user login
# - Should work with Firebase auth

# 4. Create/edit projects
# - Should persist to Firestore, not localStorage

# 5. Verify no errors
# - No red errors in console
# - Only warnings (if any) should be legitimate
```

---

## üîß Developer Notes

### Data Flow Changed
```
OLD: Component ‚Üí Store ‚Üí BackendService ‚Üí localStorage
NEW: Component ‚Üí Store ‚Üí Firebase Service ‚Üí Firestore
```

### User Store Example
```typescript
// OLD (removed)
const users = await backendService.getUsers();

// NEW (added)
import { getUsers } from '@/services/userService';
const users = await getUsers(); // Fetches from Firestore
```

### App Initialization
```typescript
// OLD - removed this line:
await backendService.initialize();

// NEW - Firebase handles it automatically
// No initialization needed
```

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Important Notes

1. **No localStorage backup** - All data now in Firestore (cloud)
2. **Real-time sync enabled** - Changes reflect immediately
3. **Auth required** - All data access requires Firebase auth
4. **No more mock data** - Initial data comes from Firestore

